==Chinese==
[[Simplified Chinese]]: 一分耕耘,一分收获
[[Traditional Chinese]]: 一分耕耘,一分收穫
[[Pinyin]]: yī fēn gēng yún, yī fēn shōu hùo
# {{idiom}} You get out of it what you put into it.
# {{idiom}} The more one works at something, the better the results.
==Etymology==
Literally: For each part sewn, one part is reaped.
